I have noticed that someone might have some trouble with the install and hardware. So this could be a help for new seeders:

System Requirements
Win 98/98SE/ME/2K/XP; Pentium III / Athlon class 450 Mhz; 128MB RAM; 32 MB Open GL 1.4 compatible PCI or AGP 3D Hardware Accelerator Required; DirectX 8-9; 16-bit DirectX 9.0a compatible sound card 

1. you need to have deamons tool, which is a "No-cd"-program that let you run the game without a cd. To do that you have to mount this game´s cue file, when you are done with downloading, you can search this program in google. It happens that somone cant get the daemon tool that is packed with the game to work.

2. When you have downloaded the game, use Winrar to unpack it.
3. Now you have to mount the Cue file in CD-1, make sure you always use the cue file in CD-1 when you install or run the game. Now you have mounted the Cue file. Go to "my computer" in Start meny. You will now see the image of the 
starwars file, klick on it. the install process has begun. through the installing progress it will ask for a second CD-disk. Now mount the other cue file from the CD-2 mapp into your Deamon again. Now the install is complete. Mount the CD-1 cue file. You don´t have to crack the game to make the multiplayer part work, only with single player.

3 Installing completed, now you have to crack the game. All the installed files should now be in C/programs/lucasarts. To crack the game ,just copy the image  "jasp". then replace it with the other "jasp"-file.
4. Now you are up and running. Have fun=) and may the force be with you..lol xD
